## Per-finding verification trail

### #1 Copy-text on linkified spans
- Code path: frontend/src/lib/linkify.ts (linkifyToHtml: file segment
  emits `<a href="${href}" data-link-kind="file">${displayText}</a>`).
- For workspace-relative paths the `href` is the resolved file://
  URL; the anchor's inner text is the displayText (the relative path
  the tool printed).
- frontend/src/lib/components/conversation/MessageTurn.svelte:416 and
  ToolOutput.svelte:223 render via `{@html sanitizeHtml(linkifyToHtml(...))}`.
- sanitize.ts allowlists `data-link-kind` and `file://` href; does not
  install a `copy` event handler.
- Default browser semantics: selection-copy on `<a>` text places the
  innerText in the plaintext clipboard; the href only surfaces under
  right-click → "Copy Link Address" (which is not what the spec
  addresses) or rich-text/HTML clipboard payloads.
- The audit's literal claim ("copying gives the file:/// href, not the
  visible text") does not reproduce under default selection-copy
  semantics. Marking STILL_OPEN per audit caution; the executor needs
  to either (a) reproduce the audit's failure mode and add a copy
  intercept, or (b) add a regression test that pins selection-copy to
  the displayText so the spec guarantee is anchored regardless of any
  future renderer change.

### #2 ANSI passthrough
- DOMPurify config in sanitize.ts removes any non-allowlisted tags;
  ANSI escapes (`\x1b[...m`) are bytes, not tags, so DOMPurify does
  NOT strip them — they are preserved in the output string. They do
  however render literally as the byte sequence (no colourisation),
  matching the linkifier note "ANSI escape sequences are passed
  through unchanged; this feature does not introduce ANSI colorisation."
- BUT tool-output-streaming.md §"What the user does NOT see" says:
  "ANSI color codes the tool emits are rendered as colored text
  inline". No code in the conversation rendering path translates ANSI
  escapes to coloured spans. Confirmed: no `ansi-to-html`,
  `anser`, or hand-rolled ANSI parser anywhere in frontend/src/.
- Audit's claim "DOMPurify strips ANSI escapes" is technically wrong
  about the mechanism (DOMPurify operates on tags/attrs, not byte
  patterns) but the user-observable behaviour matches: bash output
  loses colour. STILL_OPEN against the spec.

### #3 Soft-cap expander missing
- runner.py L489-528 implements only the hard cap
  (`STREAM_MAX_TOOL_OUTPUT_CHARS` + `STREAM_TRUNCATION_MARKER_TEMPLATE`).
- frontend/src/lib/stores/conversation.svelte.ts has a soft cap
  (`CHAT_TOOL_OUTPUT_SOFT_CAP_CHARS = 8000`) at L365-367 (hydration)
  and L770-773 (live tool_output_delta) — but it slices to the LAST N
  chars (head-truncating, not middle-folding). No "Show full output"
  expander surface is wired anywhere in ToolOutput.svelte.
- Spec wants: head AND tail bookends visible, middle collapsed,
  inline expander to reveal the full body. Implementation has tail
  only, no expander, no full-body retrieval path. STILL_OPEN.

### #4 [stopped] annotation missing
- Grep for `\[stopped\]` and `stoppedAnnotation` across
