- MessageTurn.svelte renders no annotation badge for stopped turns.
- Confirmed missing on both backend and frontend. STILL_OPEN.

### #5 Stop undo semantics inverted
- StopUndoInline.svelte:84-103: `handleStop` arms a grace-window
  setTimeout (STOP_UNDO_GRACE_MS) and only POSTs `/stop` when the
  timer expires; `handleUndo` clears the timers and aborts the POST.
- Spec semantics: stop fires, then "undo stop" lets the user re-issue
  the same prompt.
- Implementation is the opposite: stop is debounced; Undo cancels the
  pending stop. Verbatim audit claim. STILL_OPEN.
- Note: gap-cycle-11-002 (cited in the file's docstring) introduced
  the grace-window. That cycle apparently did NOT match the spec text
  — verifier flags this as a spec/implementation divergence the
  Closer must reconcile (likely by either rewriting the component to
  match the spec's stop-then-redrive model, or amending the spec to
  document the grace-window behaviour as the canonical one).

### #6 ToolProgress event dead code
- events.py L121-128 defines `ToolProgress(type='tool_progress',
  tool_call_id, elapsed_ms)`.
- Grep for `ToolProgress(` and `tool_progress` across src/bearings:
  only events.py defines it; no other module emits it via
  runner.emit() or any factory. Tests construct it manually in
  test_session_events.py and test_streaming_unit.py, but no
  production path emits.
- Frontend conversation.svelte.ts L788-792 has a reducer for
  type==='tool_progress' that updates `liveElapsedMs` — this consumer
  exists but its corresponding producer does not.
- ToolOutput.svelte L93-115 ticks elapsed via local `setInterval`
  only; the comment claims this is a "floor" against the
  server-authoritative tick that does not exist in HEAD.
- STILL_OPEN.

### #7 Elapsed timer inflates on long-disconnect replay
- ToolCallStart event (events.py:86-98) carries no `started_at`
  server timestamp.
- conversation.svelte.ts L757 sets `startedAt: Date.now()` when the
  reducer FIRST sees a tool_call_start; L741 makes the reducer
  idempotent (existing tool_call entry is preserved). Therefore on a
  disconnect-then-replay, `startedAt` retains the original receive
  time; while the disconnect was open, `nowMs` advances; on
  reconnect, `Math.max(nowMs - startedAt, liveElapsedMs)` produces
  the inflated value.
- Heartbeat frames (web/serialize.py:107-109, web/streaming.py:148)
  carry `{kind:"heartbeat", ts:<float>}` — no `tool_call_id`, not
  ring-buffered, not consumed by the conversation reducer.
- Audit text reproduced. STILL_OPEN. Coupled with #6 — fixing #6
  (emit ToolProgress per-tool with elapsed_ms) is the natural
  surface for the server-authoritative elapsed floor.

### #8 Tool-work drawer always starts open
- MessageTurn.svelte:425: `<details ... open bind:this={toolWorkEl}>`.
- Spec says drawer is collapsible; "drawer was collapsed during the
  streaming turn" is described as a reachable user state in
  tool-output-streaming.md §Scroll-anchor and chat.md §"What a
  message turn looks like" (the "⤴ TOOLS" jump button is described
  for that case).
- Hard-coding `open` on the `<details>` makes the collapsed-during-
  streaming path unreachable on first render. STILL_OPEN.

